<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1438,1338,2022]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1338,1364]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Remarks:</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[422,566,1339,1364]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[422,566,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe and west Africa was taken in the broad sense by 
<bibRefCitation author="Aartsen" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refString="Aartsen, J. J. van (1977) European Pyramidellidae: I. Chrysallida. Conchiglie, 13, 49 - 64." type="journal article" year="1977">
Aartsen (
<number box="[160,224,1378,1404]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1977.0">1977</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Linden" box="[294,675,1378,1404]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Linden, J. van der &amp; Eikenboom, J. C. A. (1992.) On the taxonomy of the Recent species of the genus Chrysallida Carpenter from Europe, the Canary Islands and the Azores (Gastropoda, Pyramidellidae). Basteria, 56, 3 - 63." type="journal article" year="1992">
Linden and Eikenboom (
<number box="[600,666,1378,1404]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who included some species with strong axial ribs crossed by prominent spiral cords, and some species without. The concept of 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1100,1417,1442]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[958,1100,1417,1442]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was restricted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schander" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Schander, C. (1994) Twenty-eight new species of Pyramidellidae (Gastropoda, Heterobranchia) from West Africa. Notiziario Centro Italiano Studi Malacologici, 15, 11 - 78." type="journal article" year="1994">
Schander (
<number box="[159,220,1455,1481]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based on protoconch shape and external anatomy, and he reintroduced the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1177,1327,1455,1480]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Odostomella" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1177,1327,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Odostomella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for those species with strong axial ribs but no spiral sculpture. Schander's (
<number box="[922,983,1494,1520]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1994.0">1994</number>
) opinion was followed by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Penas, A., Templado, J. &amp; Martinez, J. L. (1996) Contribucion al conocimiento de los Pyramidelloidea (Gastropoda: Heterostropha) del Mediterraneo espanol. Iberus, 14, 1 - 82." type="journal article">
Peñas 
<emphasis box="[1377,1436,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[160,224,1532,1558]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
; see discussion of 
<taxonomicName box="[450,600,1532,1557]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Odostomella" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[450,600,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Odostomella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1438,1338,2022]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
<bibRefCitation author="Schander" box="[198,402,1571,1597]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Schander, C. (1994) Twenty-eight new species of Pyramidellidae (Gastropoda, Heterobranchia) from West Africa. Notiziario Centro Italiano Studi Malacologici, 15, 11 - 78." type="journal article" year="1994">
Schander (
<number box="[330,393,1571,1597]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[421,661,1571,1597]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Penas, A., Templado, J. &amp; Martinez, J. L. (1996) Contribucion al conocimiento de los Pyramidelloidea (Gastropoda: Heterostropha) del Mediterraneo espanol. Iberus, 14, 1 - 82." type="journal article">
Peñas 
<emphasis box="[504,569,1571,1596]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[592,653,1571,1597]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Penas" box="[732,1036,1571,1597]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Penas, A. &amp; Rolan, E. (1998) La familia Pyramidellidae Gray, 1840 (Mollusca, Gastropoda) en Africa Occidental. 3. El genero Chrysallida s. l. Iberus, Suplemento 4, 1 - 73." type="journal article" year="1998">
Peñas and Rolán (
<number box="[964,1027,1571,1597]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, although excluding the species regarded as 
<taxonomicName box="[292,442,1610,1635]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Odostomella" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[292,442,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Odostomella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, kept using 
<taxonomicName box="[584,722,1610,1635]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[584,722,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a somewhat wide sense, including shells with strong axial and spiral cords forming a clathrate sculpture, as well as shells with strong, sinuous axial ribs crossed by weaker spiral cords, in most cases restricted to anterior region of the whorls; compare, for instance 
<taxonomicName authority="Nordsieck &amp; Garcia-Talavera" authorityName="Nordsieck &amp; Garcia-Talavera" box="[151,851,1726,1752]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis box="[151,461,1726,1751]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida canariensis</emphasis>
Nordsieck &amp; García-Talavera
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Penas" box="[895,1370,1726,1752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Penas, A. &amp; Rolan, E. (1998) La familia Pyramidellidae Gray, 1840 (Mollusca, Gastropoda) en Africa Occidental. 3. El genero Chrysallida s. l. Iberus, Suplemento 4, 1 - 73." type="journal article" year="1998">
Peñas and Rolán (
<number box="[1130,1200,1726,1752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1998.0">1998</number>
: figs. 
<number box="[1280,1362,1726,1752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="17.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="14.0">14–21</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeffreys" authorityName="Jeffreys" box="[151,719,1764,1790]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="multicostata" subGenus="Parthenina">
<emphasis box="[151,290,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[306,438,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Parthenina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[455,600,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">multicostata</emphasis>
(Jeffreys)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Aartsen" box="[756,993,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refString="Aartsen, J. J. van, Gittenberger, E. &amp; Goud, J. (2000) Pyramidellidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Heterobranchia) collected during the Dutch CANCAP and MAURITANIA expeditions in the south-eastern part of the North Atlantic Ocean (part 2). Zoologische Mededelingen, 74, 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="2000">
Aartsen 
<emphasis box="[855,907,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[929,993,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1005,1037,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="29.0">29</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[1096,1127,1764,1790]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="34.0">34</number>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1438,1338,2022]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
<bibRefCitation author="Penas" box="[198,487,1803,1829]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Penas, A. &amp; Rolan, E. (1998) La familia Pyramidellidae Gray, 1840 (Mollusca, Gastropoda) en Africa Occidental. 3. El genero Chrysallida s. l. Iberus, Suplemento 4, 1 - 73." type="journal article" year="1998">
Peñas and Rolán (
<number box="[417,478,1803,1829]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
discussed such approaches of considering 
<taxonomicName box="[1005,1143,1803,1828]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1005,1143,1803,1828]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in strict or broad sense, choosing for the broad one. The same option was taken by 
<bibRefCitation box="[842,1086,1842,1868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refString="Aartsen, J. J. van, Gittenberger, E. &amp; Goud, J. (2000) Pyramidellidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Heterobranchia) collected during the Dutch CANCAP and MAURITANIA expeditions in the south-eastern part of the North Atlantic Ocean (part 2). Zoologische Mededelingen, 74, 1 - 50." type="journal article">
Aartsen 
<emphasis box="[940,991,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1014,1078,1842,1868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who, on the other hand, used several subgenera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1438,1338,2022]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,152,719]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
In the strict sense, 
<taxonomicName box="[419,557,1919,1944]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[419,557,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is defined, after its 
<typeStatus box="[792,843,1919,1945]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1215,1919,1944]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis box="[950,1215,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Dall" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Dall, W. H. &amp; Bartsch, P. (1909) A monograph of West American Pyramidellid mollusks. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, Washington, 68, xii + 258 pp., 30 pls." type="book" year="1909">
Dall and Bartsch (
<number box="[313,376,1958,1984]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1909.0">1909</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
with the new name 
<taxonomicName authority="Dall &amp; Bartsch, 1909" authorityName="Dall &amp; Bartsch" authorityYear="1909" box="[633,1138,1958,1984]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="torrita">
<emphasis box="[633,864,1958,1983]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Chrysallida torrita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dall" box="[873,1138,1958,1984]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" refString="Dall, W. H. &amp; Bartsch, P. (1909) A monograph of West American Pyramidellid mollusks. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, Washington, 68, xii + 258 pp., 30 pls." type="book" year="1909">
Dall &amp; Bartsch, 
<number box="[1075,1138,1958,1984]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="1909.0">1909</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as shells with axial and spiral sculpture of equal strength, forming small nodules. 
<bibRefCitation box="[829,1089,1996,2022]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Schander, C. S., Halanych, K. M., Dahlgren, T. &amp; Sundberg, P. (2003) Test of the monophyly of Odostomiinae and Turbonillinae (Gastropoda, Heterobranchia, Pyramidellidae) based on 16 S mtDNA sequences. Zoologica Scripta, 32, 243 - 254." type="journal article">
Schander 
<emphasis box="[945,1004,1996,2021]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1020,1082,1996,2022]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
use the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1394,1996,2021]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Parthenina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1262,1394,1996,2021]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Parthenina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for European species usually included in 
<taxonomicName box="[600,739,152,177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[600,739,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in fact, 
<bibRefCitation box="[846,1093,152,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="63" refString="Aartsen, J. J. van, Gittenberger, E. &amp; Goud, J. (2000) Pyramidellidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Heterobranchia) collected during the Dutch CANCAP and MAURITANIA expeditions in the south-eastern part of the North Atlantic Ocean (part 2). Zoologische Mededelingen, 74, 1 - 50." type="journal article">
Aartsen 
<emphasis box="[946,999,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1022,1084,152,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
used this name as subgenus, but they stated that “the status of that nominal taxon is impossible to decide at present”. Similarly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Penas" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" refString="Penas, A. &amp; Rolan, E. (1998) La familia Pyramidellidae Gray, 1840 (Mollusca, Gastropoda) en Africa Occidental. 3. El genero Chrysallida s. l. Iberus, Suplemento 4, 1 - 73." type="journal article" year="1998">
Peñas and Rolán (
<number box="[239,301,229,255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that they used the broad sense of 
<taxonomicName box="[800,941,229,254]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[800,941,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, avoiding subgenera, while phylogenetic studies could define the taxa at genus level. Finally, 
<bibRefCitation box="[824,1112,268,294]" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" refString="Schander, C. S., Halanych, K. M., Dahlgren, T. &amp; Sundberg, P. (2003) Test of the monophyly of Odostomiinae and Turbonillinae (Gastropoda, Heterobranchia, Pyramidellidae) based on 16 S mtDNA sequences. Zoologica Scripta, 32, 243 - 254." type="journal article">
Schander 
<emphasis box="[950,1016,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1034,1103,268,294]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on the results of a phylogenetic analysis, considered 
<taxonomicName box="[563,697,306,331]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Parthenina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[563,697,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Parthenina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a full genus, including 
<taxonomicName authority="J. Adams" authorityName="J. Adams" box="[1017,1326,306,332]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="interstincta">
<emphasis box="[1017,1183,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. interstincta</emphasis>
(J. Adams)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nordsieck" authorityName="Nordsieck" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Parthenina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sarsii">
<emphasis box="[1339,1437,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. sarsii</emphasis>
(Nordsieck)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nordsieck" authorityName="Nordsieck" box="[356,655,345,371]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Parthenina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="afectuosa">
<emphasis box="[356,502,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. afectuosa</emphasis>
(Nordsieck)
</taxonomicName>
(see discussion below, under 
<taxonomicName box="[1020,1156,345,370]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Parthenina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1020,1156,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Parthenina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Herein, we adopt the strict concept of 
<taxonomicName box="[348,487,384,409]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[348,487,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, following the opinion of 
<bibRefCitation box="[796,1069,384,410]" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" refString="Schander, C., Aartsen, J. J. van &amp; Corgan, J. (1999 a.) Families and genera of the Pyramidelloidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, 34, 145 - 166." type="journal article">
Schander 
<emphasis box="[912,972,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[987,1048,384,410]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1999.0">1999</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
who argued in favor of a more detailed 
<taxonomicName box="[263,458,422,448]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Pyramidellidae</taxonomicName>
classification, rather than a minimal division, since it should include some monophyletic groups. In fact, most of phylogenetic analysis indicates that some taxa, elsewhere used as subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[307,451,500,525]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[307,451,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, deserve generic status (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wise" box="[812,946,500,526]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" refString="Wise, J. B. (1996) Morphology and phylogenetic relationships of certain pyramidellid taxa (Heterobranchia). Malacologia, 37, 443 - 551." type="journal article" year="1996">
Wise 
<number box="[882,946,500,526]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, for 
<taxonomicName authority="Schander et al. 1999" authorityName="Schander et al." authorityYear="1999" box="[1004,1371,500,526]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Boonea" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1004,1097,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Boonea</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schander" box="[1114,1371,500,526]" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" refString="Schander, C. S., Hori, S. &amp; Lundberg, J. (1999 b) Anatomy, phylogeny and biology of Odostomella and Herviera, with the description of a new species of Odostomella (Mollusca, Heterostropha, Pyramidellidae). Ophelia, 51, 39 - 76." type="journal article" year="1999" yearSuffix="b">
Schander 
<emphasis box="[1236,1299,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1308,1371,500,526]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
b, for 
<taxonomicName authority="Schander et al. 2003" authorityName="Schander et al." authorityYear="2003" box="[151,558,538,564]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Odostomella" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,301,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Odostomella</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schander" box="[315,558,538,564]" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" refString="Schander, C. S., Halanych, K. M., Dahlgren, T. &amp; Sundberg, P. (2003) Test of the monophyly of Odostomiinae and Turbonillinae (Gastropoda, Heterobranchia, Pyramidellidae) based on 16 S mtDNA sequences. Zoologica Scripta, 32, 243 - 254." type="journal article" year="2003">
Schander 
<emphasis box="[431,490,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[497,558,538,564]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, for 
<taxonomicName box="[612,744,538,563]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Parthenina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[612,744,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Parthenina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[240,315,577,603]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, there are three species listed in this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Rios" box="[838,966,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="65" refString="Rios E. C. (1994) Seashells of Brazil. 2 nd ed, Museu Oceanografico Prof. E. C. Rios da Fundacao Universidade de Rio Grande, Rio Grande, 368 pp., 113 pls." type="book" year="1994">
Rios 
<number box="[902,966,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="C. B. Adams, 1850" authorityName="C. B. Adams" authorityYear="1850" box="[987,1396,577,603]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gemmulosa">
<emphasis box="[987,1156,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">C. gemmulosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Adams" box="[1165,1396,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="63" refString="Adams, C. B. (1850) Descriptions of supposed new species which inhabit Jamaica. Contributions to Conchology, 5, 69 - 75." type="journal article" year="1850">
C. B. Adams, 
<number box="[1335,1396,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1850.0">1850</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Boonea" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jadisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">C. jadisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Olsson &amp; McGinty, 1958" authorityName="Olsson &amp; McGinty" authorityYear="1958" box="[275,746,616,642]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="toroensis">
<emphasis box="[275,416,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">C. toroensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Olsson" box="[432,737,616,642]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" refString="Olsson, A. A. &amp; McGinty, T. L. (1958) Recent marine mollusks from the Caribbean coast of Panama with descriptions of some new genera and species. Bulletin of American Paleontology, 39, 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="1958">
Olsson &amp; McGinty, 
<number box="[674,737,616,642]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1958.0">1958</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This last species is synonimized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Morch, 1876" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1876" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Mumiola" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gradatula">
<emphasis box="[1206,1436,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Mumiola gradatula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Morch" box="[159,329,654,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" refString="Morch, O. A. L. (1876) Synopsis Molluscorum marinorum Indiarum occidentalium imprimis insularum danicarum. Malacozoolische Blallter, 23, 45 - 58." type="journal article" year="1876">
Mörch, 
<number box="[261,329,654,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, following 
<bibRefCitation author="Faber" box="[486,657,654,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" refString="Faber, M. J. (2005) The Caribbean marine gastropods described by Otto Andreas Lawson Morch. 1: some type specimens and identifications (Gastropoda: Prosobranchia). Miscellanea Malacologica, 1, 81 - 99" type="journal article" year="2005">
Faber (
<number box="[578,648,654,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
; see discussion below. Following 
<bibRefCitation author="Wise" box="[1097,1258,654,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" refString="Wise, J. B. (2001) Anatomy of Boonea jadisi (Olsson &amp; McGinty, 1958) (Heterobranchia: Pyramidellidae) from the western Atlantic, with comparisons to other species in the genus. The Nautilus, 115, 68 - 75." type="journal article" year="2001">
Wise (
<number box="[1179,1248,654,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, we adopt the combination 
<taxonomicName box="[305,466,693,718]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Boonea" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jadisi">
<emphasis box="[305,466,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Boonea jadisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as discussed above).
</paragraph>
